metadata.name: I DREAMT OF DEATH; AGAIN
metadata.description:
I slept, and in my dream,  
I saw a dark and eerie place where no light shined,  
A place shadows lurked and whispered low,  
And every step I took was met with woe.

But then I saw a glimmer in the dark,  
A faint and distant spark, seemed like light,  
And as I moved closer, it grew brighter,  
A glimmer of hope in the deathly night.

And then I knew I'd make it through,  
That I would wield the light and start anew,  
For even in the darkest depths of hell,  
There's always a way to break the spell.
